 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uelaa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elaa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/1/02 2:35:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3412.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> ddubois: <i> No matter how many times you assert this, that doesn't make it so. You're going to keep going around in circles with this argument (of semantics, mostly) if you fail to recognize you cannot merely negate the effect of styles and poison.</i><br>
<br>
This is exactly the kind of response that I was talking about that shows up in a constructive post meant to talk about Left Axe and Shadowblades, and someone gets starts posting stuff that strays from the main topic.<br>
<br>
ddubois, I will say this again, a 37.5% chance to swing with offhand will increase overall melee damage by that amount. Styles and poisons are extra, they have to be worked out after the baselines of both types of offhand specializations are normalized. Otherwise, you are trying to balance Style damage to the base damage of a different kind of offhand weapon equation, and is much more difficult to quantify.<br>
<br>
There is a very good reason why I leave out style damage from the overall damage output. It is because it is something that equally affects both DW/CD and LA users. Once base damage is normalized first, THEN you can move on and compare styles and equal those. If you do the reverse and compare styles first, THEN it may result in a situation where a single style becomes the equilizer for the entire specialization (ie Doubleforst again).<br>
<br>
You can argue all you want that +75 weapon damage due to a style to the primary in either DW/CD or LA is going to result in a shift in the damage increase from using one weapon. That will definately happen. However, if you check the baselines and match them, and then +75 weapon damage is added from a style, then you've reached something rather balancing.<br>
<br>
Also, the chance to hit with the primary weapon in RvR with +hit styles is exaggerated. This is because of the order of the checks that go into place. For example, a +hit bonus has no effect against an enemy's chance to parry/block/evade/bubble. The +hit affects your first hit that checks to see if miss the enemy or not. This is a great factor in that I cannot pull off my 4-chain Evade combo in RvR, despite that it has large +hit bonuses. I can get past the miss check, but it always gets parried/blocked/evaded by the 2-3 attack and ending the chain. Unless I am a 50 Thrust Infiltrator that used Dragonfang to open the combo, there's no way I can pull it off.<br>
<br>
<i>I'll end with an admittedly silly example to drive the point home: If I swing my primary weapon 100% of the time hitting every swing for 100 damage each, and my offhand weapon 37.5% of the time hitting every swing for 1 damage each, is my offhand weapon contributing 37.5% of my overall damage output?</i><br>
<br>
And what if you chose a superior weapon in your offhand, and a lesser weapon in your primary (which is more true for DW/CD users that have to keep switching primaries). I take the averages, and not special cases.<br>
<br>
<br>
I'm done talking about theory and what if's, I take the laws of averages and use them in my calculations. A level 50 Shadowblade failed on the perf today and hit me for 29 and 40 damage. Granted I have 26% slash resist (only 11% after leather penalty). I ran only because I was scouting a keep that he was defending. I take things from math, statistics, and experience.<br>
<br>
I'm done respondig to posts like this, it wastes too much of my time. They stray from the point and are even wrong on the points they are trying to argue.  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uelaa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elaa</A> at: 6/1/02 2:46:02 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uddubois.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ddubois</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/1/02 3:24:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3412.topic&index=40>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> I'm done respondig to posts like this, it wastes too much of my time</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
