I don't think I implied that at all.  What I am saying, and have said, that comparing some small facet of the classes is less worthwhile than comparing their overall damage output, and the other factors of the class.  I also feel pretty strongly people shouldn't refer to base damage as &quot;Overall damage output&quot;, because that's just flat-out misleading.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  So if you want to balance the two classes obviously you have to balance #3</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
That's not obvious to me.  You could easily balance the classes by adding some other difference #6, or improving the margin of favor for SBs in 1, 2, 4 or 5.  Which you amusingly continue on to suggest later in your post.<br>
<br>
I don't want to get dragged in over my head.  To be honest, I haven't the slightest idea how balanced infiltrators are versus SBs or NSs.  The reason I jumped into this thread was the references to increases in offhand swings have a linear correlation to &quot;Overall damage output&quot;, and the anal-retentive side of me couldn't let it slide.  Sorry to have stirred up such a frenzy on this issue, it's really not worth it.<br>
